My family and I go every Sunday after Church and we love this place. In the world of chains like Ihop and The Good egg with their grumpy servers and mundane food, this place is a welcome change. Yes, the place is small and the bathroom is tiny and behind the kitchen (really, who cares, I don't come for the toilet) - biscuits and gravy are great and the servers are efficient and friendly. Never had a bad breakfast there.

