I used to come here when I lived in Phoenix for the beer and wings- with a buddy from Buffalo so this place is legit. Great beer list, changes regularly- a 10% ABV Imperial Ale in a chalice? Yes please. Wings are the best in Phoenix (try Teakwoods too but get the Thai Cina) Food was great, came with a bunch of coworkers for a meeting. An all day meeting. An all day meeting around Big Data, and I'm the only non-iT nerd there. So sure, I'm a nerd to, but an Ops nerd and I consider these other self professed nerds friends but when the waitress keeps bringing you said delicious IPAs and you are enjoying the vibe- remember Big Data and Big Beers do not go well together! But seriously, nice atmosphere, clean, good choices, service and well priced. Check it out.

